                                <title2_copy
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1651545824678,1651545825694]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2025-09-15T12:30:51.965-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    jcr:title="Effects on mental health"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/title/v2/title"
                                    type="h2"
                                    variant="h"/>
                                <text2
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1659545835858]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2025-09-15T16:50:02.451-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>Because symptoms can be subtle, easily overlooked or mistaken for other conditions, ovarian cancer is rarely diagnosed early. On top of that, recurrence rates are high—hovering around 80%&lt;sup>2&lt;/sup>—creating conditions that can, for many women, stoke fear and anxieties.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>While mental health is as important to women with ovarian cancer as their physical health for their quality of life, it often gets overlooked, according to the World Ovarian Cancer Coalition’s &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.international-journal-of-gynecological-cancer.com/article/S1048-891X(24)02278-3/fulltext&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>Every Woman Study&lt;/a>, which surveyed more than 1,500 women with ovarian cancer globally. In their survey, just 28% of women say they were offered support by a healthcare professional for their mental health.&lt;sup>1&lt;/sup>&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                            </container4>
                            <image
                                jcr:created="{Date}2025-09-15T12:31:22.979-04:00"
                                jcr:createdBy="VALENSX5"
                                jcr:lastModified="{Date}2025-09-16T09:50:51.412-04:00"
                                jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
