                        <par_12
                            jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                            sling:resourceType="wcm/foundation/components/parsys">
                            <container4
                                cq:styleIds="[1653545847150,1653242825678,1653545825687,1653545835982]"
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/container/v2/container">
                                <title2_copy
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1651545824678,1651545825694]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2025-09-15T12:32:10.921-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    jcr:title="Altering relationships with family and community"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/title/v2/title"
                                    type="h2"
                                    variant="h"/>
                                <text2
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1659545835858]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2025-09-15T12:32:26.680-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>Managing life with ovarian cancer can also alter social connections for many women. For some it can be isolating, and for others it can demand a complete shift in how they interact with friends and family. For Carolyn, it meant having to completely rethink where she could go, what she could eat and when.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>“Socially, I have to really think about what I’m going into. Has the place got stairs? Are we going out to dinner somewhere that I can eat? If I’m going away, does it fit with the chemotherapy cycle?” she says. “It’s just layers of complexity on what you do every day.”&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                            </container4>
                            <image
                                jcr:created="{Date}2025-09-15T12:31:22.979-04:00"
                                jcr:createdBy="VALENSX5"
